
 
 Method Reference in Java 8 - Interview Definition
	

	Definition:

	A Method Reference is a feature introduced in Java 8 that allows us to refer to an 
	existing method by its name instead of writing a lambda expression. 
	It is used when the lambda expression only calls an 
	existing method, making the code 
	more readable and concise.
	
	syntax
	
	ClassName::methodName
	
	objectReference::methodName
	

	